FPGA Transformer Accelerator — GPT-2 on Alveo U280
====================================================

Fixed-point transformer inference engine targeting Xilinx Alveo U280.
INT16 datapath, INT32 accumulation, HBM2 memory hierarchy.
GPT-2 Medium (1024-dim, 16 heads, 24 layers, 4096 FFN) with KV cache decode.

Architecture
------------
Compute:
  - 2x parallel 32x32 tiled matmul engines (1024 mac_units each, DSP48E2 mapped)
  - Tiling engine dispatches (M,N) tile pairs round-robin to idle engines
  - Per-engine tile loaders issue AXI4 read bursts from HBM (weight + activation)
  - URAM accumulation buffer (1024x4096 x INT16) with write arbiter backpressure

Memory hierarchy:
  - HBM2 (8 GB, 32 channels): weight storage, activation storage, output
  - URAM: on-chip accumulation buffer + non-matmul staging area
  - Per-engine tile loaders (64-word local buffer, blocking load-then-compute)
  - URAM flush controller (URAM -> HBM via AXI4 write bursts)

Non-matmul path:
  - Scalar NM adapter (16-bit <-> 256-bit URAM bridge, read cache + write buffer)
  - act_dma (scalar <-> HBM bridge for LN params, residual skip connections)
  - Softmax (3-pass, exp/recip LUTs, causal masking, attention scaling)
  - LayerNorm (3-pass, BRAM input buffer, 2-stage normalize pipeline)
  - ReLU activation, saturating residual add

Control:
  - FSM controller (step-table architecture, GPT-2 pre-norm program)
  - Host interface (AXI-Lite) or Vitis ap_ctrl_hs (FPGA target)
  - KV cache decode mode (prefill + autoregressive single-token decode)

FPGA deployment (Alveo U280):
  - 6 AXI4 master ports to HBM (2 wgt, 2 act, 1 flush, 1 DMA)
  - Vitis RTL kernel packaging (.xo) via build.tcl
  - v++ link with AltSpreadLogic_high placement directive (148 MHz achieved)
  - XRT host application for GPT-2 medium text generation

Repository Structure
--------------------
  rtl/              RTL source files (~9000 lines, Verilator-compatible)
    defines.vh        Centralized parameters (dimensions, bus widths, FSM states)
    top_level.v       Top-level: generates engines, wires shared infrastructure
    fsm_controller.v  Step-table FSM orchestrator (GPT-2 pre-norm / post-norm)
    host_interface.v  AXI-Lite slave (simulation only)
    matmul_engine.v   32x32 outer-product MAC engine + per-engine controller
    mac_unit.v        Single pipelined MAC (3-stage, DSP48E2 target)
    agu.v             Address generation for tiled matmul
    tiling_engine.v   Master tile dispatcher (N engines)
    tile_loader.v     HBM -> local buffer AXI4 read loader
    mem_arbiter.v     Round-robin arbiter for multi-engine activation BRAM
    uram_accum_buf.v  URAM output buffer with write serialization
    uram_flush.v      URAM -> HBM flush via AXI4 write bursts
    uram_nm_adapter.v Scalar <-> URAM bus-width bridge
    act_dma.v         Scalar <-> HBM DMA bridge
    sim_hbm_port.v    HBM simulation stub (not synthesized)
    softmax.v         3-pass softmax with causal masking
    layernorm.v       3-pass layer normalization (BRAM-buffered)
    activation.v      ReLU activation
    residual_add.v    Saturating residual addition
    quant_layer.v     INT16 -> INT8 quantization
    positional_embedding.v  Token + position embedding addition
    bram_controller.v Legacy BRAM controller

  fpga/             FPGA build files (Alveo U280)
    rtl/
      fpga_kernel.v   Vitis RTL kernel wrapper (port renaming, addr conversion)
      vitis_control.v Vitis ap_ctrl_hs AXI-Lite slave
    kernel.xml        Vitis kernel descriptor
    connectivity.cfg  HBM bank mapping (sp= assignments)
    build.tcl         Vivado batch: package RTL -> .xo
    Makefile          Build targets: package, link-emu, link-hw, link-hw-spread
    host.cpp          XRT host: GPT-2 text generation (BPE tokenize -> FPGA -> decode)
    gpt2_bpe.h        Header-only GPT-2 BPE tokenizer (C++17)
    report.md         Build/congestion analysis notes

  tb/               Testbenches (Verilator)
    tb_top.v          Full pipeline (SIM_SMALL)
    tb_top_1k.v       Production-scale (1024-dim, SIM_1K)
    tb_top_decode.v   Decode mode (prefill + KV cache decode, SIM_1K)
    tb_top_matmul1k.v Single matmul 1024x1024
    tb_matmul.v       Matmul engine unit test
    tb_*.v            Per-module testbenches

  verify/           Co-simulation and golden model verification
    golden/           Python golden models (matmul, softmax, layernorm, etc.)
    tb_cosim/         RTL co-sim testbenches for individual modules
    run_cosim.py      Compares RTL output against golden models
    test_top.py       Full SIM_SMALL integration test
    test_top_1k.py    Production-scale 1024-dim full pipeline test
    test_matmul1k.py  1024x1024 single matmul test
    test_decode_1k.py Decode mode test (prefill seq=8 + decode seq=1)

  scripts/          Build/sim scripts
    verilator.f       Verilator flags (SIM_SMALL)
    verilator_1k.f    Verilator flags (SIM_1K)
    verilator_decode.f Verilator flags (decode mode)
    export_gpt2.py    Export GPT-2 weights to FPGA binary format

  test_ctrl/        Minimal ap_ctrl_hs test kernel (for debugging XRT handshake)

  tasks/            Project tracking
    summary.md        Module interface reference
    todo.md           Current task tracker
    lessons.md        Debugging patterns and lessons learned

Module Hierarchy
----------------
  top_level (diffusion_transformer_top)
  ├── vitis_control / host_interface    (AXI-Lite control, swapped by FPGA_TARGET)
  ├── fsm_controller                    (step-table FSM, 17 states)
  ├── tiling_engine                     (M×N tile dispatch to engines)
  ├── [per-engine ×2]:
  │   ├── tile_loader (weight)          (HBM → 64-word local BRAM)
  │   ├── tile_loader (activation)
  │   ├── sim_hbm_port ×2              (sim only, ifdef'd out for FPGA)
  │   └── matmul_controller             (K-loop + matmul_engine 32×32 MAC array)
  ├── uram_accum_buf                    (1024×4096, round-robin write arbiter)
  ├── uram_flush                        (URAM → HBM AXI4 write master)
  ├── uram_nm_adapter                   (scalar ↔ URAM, 1-word cache)
  ├── act_dma                           (scalar ↔ HBM, for params + skip)
  ├── softmax                           (3-pass, LUT exp/recip, causal mask)
  ├── layernorm                         (3-pass, BRAM buffer, 2-stage pipeline)
  ├── activation_unit                   (ReLU)
  └── residual_add                      (saturating INT16 add)

Configuration
-------------
All parameters are centralized in rtl/defines.vh. Three compile-time configs:

  SIM_SMALL:    MODEL_DIM=64,  NUM_ENGINES=2, MAX_SEQ_LEN=32  (fast sim)
  SIM_1K:       MODEL_DIM=1024, NUM_ENGINES=4, MAX_SEQ_LEN=128 (verification)
  Production:   MODEL_DIM=1024, NUM_ENGINES=2, MAX_SEQ_LEN=128 (FPGA, reduced for routing)

Fixed hardware constants:
  DATA_WIDTH    = 16      INT16 inputs/weights/outputs
  ACC_WIDTH     = 32      INT32 accumulation in MAC units
  TILE_SIZE     = 32      32×32 outer-product MAC array
  BUS_WIDTH     = 256     16 INT16 elements per AXI beat
  HBM_ADDR_W    = 28      256-bit word address, covers 8GB

Architecture selection:
  ARCHITECTURE = 0   GPT-2 Pre-Norm (LN before attention/FFN)
  ARCHITECTURE = 1   Post-Norm (LN after attention/FFN, original transformer)

HBM Memory Layout
-----------------
Weight buffer (HBM[0:3], ~576 MB for GPT-2 Medium):
  Per-layer (786,688 words × 32 bytes/word ≈ 24 MB):
    Offset 0:        W_Q   (1024×1024)
    Offset 65536:    W_K   (1024×1024)
    Offset 131072:   W_V   (1024×1024)
    Offset 196608:   W_O   (1024×1024)
    Offset 262144:   FFN1  (1024×4096)
    Offset 524288:   FFN2  (4096×1024)
    Offset 786432:   LN1 gamma/beta (2×1024 elements)
    Offset 786560:   LN2 gamma/beta (2×1024 elements)

Activation buffer (HBM[4], ~16 MB):
    ACT_EMBED:  seq×1024     Embeddings / residual output
    ACT_Q:      seq×1024     Query projections
    ACT_K:      seq×1024     Key projections (+ KV cache)
    ACT_V:      seq×1024     Value projections (+ KV cache)
    ACT_ATTN:   seq×seq      Attention scores
    ACT_TEMP:   seq×1024     Staging (LN output for pre-norm)

HBM bank assignment (connectivity.cfg):
    m_axi_hbm00/01  Read   HBM[0:3]  Weight loaders (engine 0/1)
    m_axi_hbm06/07  Read   HBM[4]    Act loaders (engine 0/1)
    m_axi_hbm12     Write  HBM[4]    URAM flush
    m_axi_hbm13     R/W    HBM[0:5]  DMA (params, skip, output)

All data is INT16, packed 16 elements per 256-bit word, row-major.

FSM Layer Program (GPT-2 Pre-Norm)
-----------------------------------
Each layer executes 16 steps from a step table (fsm_controller.v):

  Step  Block    Config  Description
  ────  ───────  ──────  ───────────────────────────
   0    LN       0       LayerNorm1 on embeddings
   1    FLUSH    1       LN1 output → ACT_TEMP
   2    QKV      1       Q/K/V matmuls (from ACT_TEMP, 3 phases)
   3    ATTN     0       Multi-head attention (score→softmax→output, 16 heads)
   4    MATMUL   0       Output projection (W_O)
   5    RES      0       Residual1 (embeddings + projected attention)
   6    FLUSH    0       Residual1 → ACT_EMBED
   7    LN       1       LayerNorm2
   8    FLUSH    1       LN2 output → ACT_TEMP
   9    MATMUL   2       FFN1 (from ACT_TEMP, 1024→4096)
  10    ACT      0       ReLU on FFN1 output
  11    FLUSH    2       FFN1 output → ACT_FFN
  12    MATMUL   3       FFN2 (4096→1024)
  13    RES      0       Residual2 (residual1 + FFN output)
  14    FLUSH    0       Residual2 → ACT_EMBED
  15    END      0       Layer done → loop or finish

Block types: BT_LN(0), BT_QKV(1), BT_ATTN(2), BT_MATMUL(3),
             BT_ACT(4), BT_RES(5), BT_FLUSH(6), BT_END(15)

Decode mode (KV cache): When decode_mode=1, only 4 states change:
  S_QKV_MM:    K/V appended at cache_len offset
  S_ATT_SCORE: Q(1×d) × K_cached^T → scores(1×cache_total)
  S_ATT_SM:    Softmax over cache_total columns, causal at row=cache_len
  S_ATT_OUT:   Scores(1×cache_total) × V_cached → output(1×d)

Changing the Model
------------------
1. Different dimensions:
   Edit rtl/defines.vh in the appropriate ifdef block. Change MODEL_DIM,
   F_DIM, NUM_HEADS. Update URAM_ROWS/COLS to fit. Weight layout offsets
   in fsm_controller.v auto-compute from MODEL_DIM and F_DIM.

2. Different architecture (pre-norm vs post-norm):
   Set ARCHITECTURE=0 (pre-norm) or ARCHITECTURE=1 (post-norm) in defines.vh.
   Each has its own step table in fsm_controller.v.

3. New architecture:
   Define a new step table (16 entries max) in fsm_controller.v:
     localparam [8*MAX_STEPS-1:0] PROG_CUSTOM = {
         {BT_END,    4'd0},   // step 15
         ...                   // your steps
         {BT_LN,     4'd0}    // step 0
     };
   Add it to the PROGRAM selection logic. If you need new block types,
   add new states to the FSM case statement.

4. Different activation:
   Replace ReLU logic in activation_unit.v. GELU needs a LUT or polynomial
   approximation (similar to softmax's exp LUT approach).

5. Add bias to matmul:
   Option A: Fuse bias into a residual_add step after each matmul
   Option B: Add bias accumulation to matmul_engine.v output stage

6. More layers / different model:
   Change NUM_ENC_LAYERS. FSM loops automatically. Weight buffer grows
   proportionally. Re-export weights with scripts/export_gpt2.py.

7. Longer sequences:
   Increase MAX_SEQ_LEN. Update URAM_ROWS if needed. Activation buffer
   grows proportionally.

Running Tests
-------------
Prerequisites: Verilator, Python 3 with numpy

  make lint               # Verilator lint check
  make cosim              # Co-sim all modules (matmul, softmax, LN, ReLU, residual)
  make cosim-matmul       # Co-sim matmul only
  make cosim-softmax      # Co-sim softmax only
  make cosim-layernorm    # Co-sim layernorm only
  make test-small         # Full SIM_SMALL pipeline (64-dim, 2 engines, ~10 min)
  make test-1k            # Production-scale full pipeline (1024-dim, ~30 min)
  make test-decode        # Decode mode (prefill seq=8 + decode seq=1, ~20 min)
  make test-matmul1k      # Single 1024x1024 matmul verification
  make sim TARGET=<module> # Run individual module testbench
  make wave               # Open gtkwave on last trace

Co-simulation system (verify/):
  Python golden models in verify/golden/ replicate exact LUT values and
  fixed-point arithmetic from RTL for bit-exact comparison. run_cosim.py
  generates random inputs, compiles RTL with Verilator, runs, and compares
  element-by-element against golden output.

Latency tolerance testing (all testbenches accept Verilator -G overrides):
  ./obj_dir/Vtb_top -GHBM_RD_LATENCY=100 -GURAM_RD_LATENCY=4
  Tested: HBM={2,5,10,100,200} × URAM={1,2,4} — all pass.

FPGA Build (Alveo U280)
------------------------
Prerequisites: Vivado 2022.2, Vitis 2022.2, XRT, U280 platform

  cd fpga/

  # Package RTL → .xo (~5 min)
  make package

  # Hardware emulation (~10 min, no FPGA needed)
  make link-emu
  make host
  make run-emu

  # Full hardware build (~7 hours)
  nohup bash -c "make package && make link-hw-spread" > synth_log 2>&1 &

  # Run on FPGA
  make host
  make run-hw

Build tips:
  - Don't make clean before rebuild — .ipcache speeds synthesis significantly
  - Check synth_log for timing (WNS). 148 MHz achieved with AltSpreadLogic_high
  - fpga/report.md has detailed SLR utilization analysis

GPT-2 Inference
---------------
1. Export weights:
    pip install torch transformers numpy
    python3 scripts/export_gpt2.py --model gpt2-medium --output-dir fpga/data/

2. Download tokenizer:
    python3 -c "from transformers import GPT2Tokenizer; \
      t=GPT2Tokenizer.from_pretrained('gpt2'); t.save_pretrained('fpga/data')"

3. Compile and run:
    cd fpga/
    make host
    source /opt/xilinx/xrt/setup.sh
    ./host fpga_kernel_hw.xclbin data/ "The meaning of life is" 50
    ./host fpga_kernel_hw.xclbin data/ "Once upon a time" 100 0.8

End-to-end flow:
  1. Host loads tokenizer (vocab.json + merges.txt)
  2. Host loads embeddings (embed.bin: wte 50257×1024, wpe 1024×1024, ln_f)
  3. Host opens U280, loads xclbin, allocates XRT buffers (576 MB wgt, 16 MB act, 4 MB out)
  4. Host loads weights.bin → HBM, syncs to device
  5. PREFILL: tokenize → embed (wte+wpe) → quantize INT16 → launch kernel
     (batch=1, seq=prompt_len, decode=0) → FPGA runs 24 layers × 16 steps
  6. Host reads output, applies ln_f (FP32), unembeds (hidden × wte^T → logits)
  7. Sample/argmax → first generated token
  8. DECODE LOOP: embed new token → launch kernel (seq=1, decode=1, cache=total_pos)
     → FPGA reuses KV cache → ln_f → unembed → sample → print token → repeat

Known Limitations
-----------------
- GELU replaced with ReLU (GPT-2 uses GELU — reduced output quality)
- No bias in matmul (GPT-2 linears have bias — skipped)
- Final LayerNorm (ln_f) runs on host CPU, not in RTL
- INT8 symmetric per-tensor weight quantization (may need per-channel for larger models)
- 128 max sequence length (increase MAX_SEQ_LEN + URAM sizing for more)
- 2 engines on FPGA (SLR0 routing congestion limits scaling)
- 148 MHz (target 200 MHz — deeper pipelining needed)
- No attention position encoding (ALiBi/RoPE not supported)
- quant_layer memory interface tied off (needs HBM adapter)
